    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce 'reading dogs' to all primary schools in England",
        "additional_details": "The Kennel Club already run a 'Bark and Read' scheme https://www.thekennelclub.org.uk/barkandread \r\nLane, H.B. & Zavada, S.D.W. 'When reading gets ruff: canine-assisted reading' The Reading Teacher 2013, 67(2) p. 87-95\r\n",
        "background": "Research shows that children can get very stressed with reading aloud in class. Reading to dogs is a good way of stopping children feeling scared - dogs do not make comments or tell you off for getting things wrong and they always listen. All primary schools should have access to a 'reading dog.'",
